					<description><![CDATA[<p>Quantum Systems Raises $1.2 Billion to Accelerate Defence Technology European drone manufacturer Quantum Systems has raised $1.2 billion in a Series D funding round to expand its autonomous defence technology</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/quantum-systems-raises-1-2b-series-d-to-expand-defence-ai/" data-wpel-link="internal">Quantum Systems Raises $1.2B Series D to Expand Defence AI</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<h2><b>Quantum Systems Raises $1.2 Billion to Accelerate Defence Technology</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">European drone manufacturer Quantum Systems has raised $1.2 billion in a Series D funding round to expand its autonomous defence technology platform. The investment values the German company at approximately $8 billion. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Blackstone, Noteus, Airbus and Advent co-led the funding round, joined by BOND, Fidelity Management &amp; Research Company, Wellington Management, A.P. Moller Holding, Elephant Lake Ventures, Balderton and HV Capital. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Founded in Munich, it builds autonomous drones for defense, security, and commercial use and already has orders from NATO troops and commercial clients in the U.S., Ukraine, and Australia.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">This round more than doubles its valuation of approximately $3.5 billion that it set in a round less than a year ago. Florian Seibel co-founder and co-CEO told reporters that the company is profitable and that the cash will fuel expansion as it now has over $1.2 billion on hand.</span></p>
<h2><b>New Funding Supports AI-Powered Multi-Domain Operations</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Quantum Systems plans to use most of the capital to strengthen its MOSAIC UXS software platform. The system links drones, sensors, counter-drone capabilities and drone ports in a shared operational network. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The integrated software will play an increasingly important role as defense organizations implement autonomous systems in several operating domains. Its systems operate on the air, on the ground and in the water using artificial intelligence and real-time data analysis.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company will use the money to expand production capacity and boost global sales, as well as continue its work on the next generation of autonomous, AI-driven systems. Co-CEO Sven Kruck stated.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Quantum Systems was founded in 2015 by Florian Seibel, a former pilot with the German Air Force (Bundeswehr). The business originally focused on agricultural surveying before shifting towards defence and intelligence solutions.</span></p>
<h2><b>Blackstone Signals Rising Confidence in European Defence</b></h2>
<div id="attachment_203319" style="width: 1322px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-203319" class="size-full wp-image-203319" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/Quantum-2.png" alt="Illustration of European autonomous aerial systems supported by institutional investment, aerospace partnerships, and AI-driven defence technology integration. " width="1312" height="736" /><p id="caption-attachment-203319" class="wp-caption-text">Rising institutional investment and strategic industry partnerships are strengthening Europe’s defence technology ecosystem, accelerating the development of autonomous systems, AI-enabled capabilities, and long-term security infrastructure. Source: Created by Ventureburn.</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The investment is notable because Blackstone rarely backs European drone companies. The asset manager oversees $1.3 trillion, reflecting growing institutional confidence in Europe&#8217;s defence technology sector.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">David Kaden described Blackstone&#8217;s investment as responding to structural changes across the European defence market. He said growing demand for advanced technologies requires long-term capital to support industry expansion and security infrastructure.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Airbus also strengthened its relationship with Quantum Systems through both investment and strategic collaboration. The partnership will combine expertise in software, artificial intelligence and defence systems to improve operational capabilities across both companies.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Quantum Systems has also expanded through acquisitions. It previously integrated AirRobot, Nordic Unmanned and Spleenlab to broaden its technology portfolio and strengthen its autonomous systems offering.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/linqalpha-raises-22-million-series-a-to-expand-ai-market-intelligence/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">LinqAlpha Raises $22 Million Series A to Expand AI Market Intelligence</span></a></p>
<h2><b>European Defence Funding Continues to Accelerate</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The latest investment reflects broader momentum across Europe&#8217;s defence technology industry. According to Dealroom and the NATO Innovation Fund, European defence, security and resilience startups attracted a record $8.7 billion during 2025. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Quantum Systems joins a growing group of European drone unicorns competing for NATO contracts. Rival defence technology company Helsing also raised $1.2 billion earlier this year, although it achieved a significantly higher </span><a href="https://corporatefinanceinstitute.com/resources/valuation/valuation/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">valuation</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> of $18 billion. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Meanwhile, several other defence technology firms continue pursuing large fundraising rounds as governments increase spending on autonomous systems. Quantum Systems combines hardware, artificial intelligence, and mission software into one integrated platform.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company believes this approach positions it well for both military and civilian markets. The fresh capital provides significant resources to expand production, strengthen research and accelerate international deployments. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">To stay updated on crypto venture capital funding and market trends, visit our </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/category/news/venture-capital/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">venture capital news section</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> for more insights.</span></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/quantum-systems-raises-1-2b-series-d-to-expand-defence-ai/" data-wpel-link="internal">Quantum Systems Raises $1.2B Series D to Expand Defence AI</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
